headline: T. Rowe Price (TROW): Evaluating Valuation After Recent Share Price Uptick
summary: T. Rowe Price Group (TROW) has quietly edged higher this month, even as longer term returns remain under pressure. That mix of recent momentum and lagging performance naturally raises a valuation question for investors. See our latest analysis for T. Rowe Price Group. Zooming out a bit, that 4.1% seven day share price return sits against a weaker year to date share price performance and a negative one year total shareholder return.
